                  <additions>
                    <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc type="ReceiptNote">
                              <locus target="#111v" facs="114">Fol. 111v</locus> Receipt of money (borrowed?), insufficiently legible</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#39r" facs="041">Fol. 39r</locus> A symbol in red and black and a short text, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝየ።መንፈቁ፡ ለዳዊት፡</foreign>“here is half of Dawit,” enclosed in a black-ink rectangle mark the midpoint of the psalms</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>
                          Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (
                          <locus target="#10r #14r #19v #23r #35r #41r" facs="012 016 022 025 037 043">folss. 10r, 14r, 19v, 23r, 35r, 41r, </locus>, etc.);
                          and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (
                          <locus target="#44v" facs="047"> f. 4vv, line 15</locus>, <locus target="#58v" facs="061"> f. 58v, line 20</locus>, <locus target="#63r" facs="065"> f. 63r, line 5</locus>, <locus target="#67r" facs="069"> f. 67r, line 4</locus>, <locus target="#89r" facs="091"> f. 89r, line 8</locus>, <locus target="#104v" facs="107"> f. 104v, line 10</locus>)
                        </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>
                          The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect
                          ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above or
                          below the end of the line (throughout). This scribe will also reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (throughout)
                        </desc>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc>The general condition of the vellum is a bit dirty and stained but relatively unworn</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#108v #109r #109v #110r #112r #112v" facs="111 112 114 115">Fols. 108v, 109r, 109v, 110r, 112r, 112v</locus> blank</desc>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
